  "text": "Attempts to control disease in wildlife populations, or to avoid disease transmission between wildlife and livestock, have been based on a variety of methods. These include setting up barriers, improving hygienic measures, culling, habitat management and feeding bans, vector control, treatments and vaccination [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
